cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SE

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on detecting malicious cyber-attacks in electronic documents. The use of machine learning and entropy signals also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of image processing techniques to extract features from the documents could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed framework through experiments and comparison with existing tools suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
